problem:
You are tasked with implementing a function that processes a given set of country data and returns a specific output based on the requirements. The country data is represented as an object `countries` with keys as country names and values as arrays containing the country's capital and official language.

You need to create a function `getCountryInfo` that takes in the `countries` object and a country name as input and returns an object with the following properties:
- `name`: the name of the country
- `capital`: the capital of the country
- `language`: the official language of the country

The function should handle cases where the input country name does not exist in the `countries` object by returning an appropriate message.

Example:
```javascript
const countries = {
  "USA": ["Washington D.C.", "English"],
  "France": ["Paris", "French"],
  "Japan": ["Tokyo", "Japanese"]
};

console.log(getCountryInfo(countries, "France"));
// Output: { name: "France", capital: "Paris", language: "French" }

console.log(getCountryInfo(countries, "Germany"));
// Output: "Country information not found"
```

solution:
```javascript
function getCountryInfo(countries, countryName) {
  if (countries.hasOwnProperty(countryName)) {
    const [capital, language] = countries[countryName];
    return { name: countryName, capital, language };
  } else {
    return "Country information not found";
  }
}
```

problem:
You are tasked with creating a function that generates HTML image tags based on a given set of styles. The styles object contains different image styles, each with a URI and alt text. Your function should take the styles object as input and return a string of HTML image tags for each style.

For example, given the following styles object:
```javascript
const styles = {
  thumbnail: {
    uri: 'https://dol.wa.com/logo.png',
    alt: 'Washington State Seal',
  },
  hero: {
    uri: 'https://dol.wa.com/people-working.png',
    alt: 'People working on serious things',
  },
};
```
The function should output the following HTML string:
```html
<img src="https://dol.wa.com/logo.png" alt="Washington State Seal">
<img src="https://dol.wa.com/people-working.png" alt="People working on serious things">
```

Write a function `generateImageTags(styles)` that takes in the styles object and returns a string of HTML image tags based on the given styles.

solution:
```javascript
function generateImageTags(styles) {
  let html = '';
  for (const style in styles) {
    if (styles.hasOwnProperty(style)) {
      const { uri, alt } = styles[style];
      html += `<img src="${uri}" alt="${alt}">`;
    }
  }
  return html;
}

// Test the function
const styles = {
  thumbnail: {
    uri: 'https://dol.wa.com/logo.png',
    alt: 'Washington State Seal',
  },
  hero: {
    uri: 'https://dol.wa.com/people-working.png',
    alt: 'People working on serious things',
  };
console.log(generateImageTags(styles));
```

The `generateImageTags` function iterates through the styles object, extracting the URI and alt text for each style and concatenating them into HTML image tags. The function then returns the concatenated HTML string.

