import re

def extractNameAndLocation(html_snippet):
    name_pattern = r'<b>(.*?), </b>'
    location_pattern = r'</b>(.*?)(<p>|<\?)'

    name_match = re.search(name_pattern, html_snippet)
    location_match = re.search(location_pattern, html_snippet)

    if name_match and location_match:
        name = name_match.group(1)
        location = location_match.group(1)
        return {"name": name, "location": location}
    else:
        return {"name": "", "location": ""}
```

The `extractNameAndLocation` function uses regular expressions to match the name and location patterns in the HTML snippet. It then returns a dictionary containing the extracted name and location information. If the patterns are not found, it returns an empty string for both name and location.
